{
  "uid": "vtop-engine",
  "title": "VTOP Engine",
  "description": "The engine itself, from its own Prometheus metrics (/metrics). Everything here is measured by VTOP, not inferred from Kafka or MinIO. Start here.",
  "tags": [
    "vtop",
    "engine"
  ],
  "timezone": "browser",
  "schemaVersion": 39,
  "version": 1,
  "refresh": "30s",
  "time": {
    "from": "now-1h",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "templating": {
    "list": [
      {
        "name": "tenant",
        "label": "Tenant",
        "type": "query",
        "datasource": {
          "type": "prometheus",
          "uid": "mimir"
        },
        "query": {
          "query": "label_values(vtop_batches_total, tenant)",
          "refId": "tenant"
        },
        "refresh": 2,
        "includeAll": true,
        "allValue": ".*",
        "multi": true,
        "current": {
          "text": "All",
          "value": "$__all"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "source_type",
        "label": "Source",
        "type": "query",
        "datasource": {
          "type": "prometheus",
          "uid": "mimir"
        },
        "query": {
          "query": "label_values(vtop_batches_total, source_type)",
          "refId": "source_type"
        },
        "refresh": 2,
        "includeAll": true,
        "allValue": ".*",
        "multi": true,
        "current": {
          "text": "All",
          "value": "$__all"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "format",
        "label": "Format",
        "type": "query",
        "datasource": {
          "type": "prometheus",
          "uid": "mimir"
        },
        "query": {
          "query": "label_values(vtop_batches_total, format)",
          "refId": "format"
        },
        "refresh": 2,
        "includeAll": true,
        "allValue": ".*",
        "multi": true,
        "current": {
          "text": "All",
          "value": "$__all"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "panels": [
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Is the engine healthy?",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "collapsed": false,
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Engine up",
      "description": "Scrape health. If this is 0 every panel below is stale \u2014 check the engine and VTOP_METRICS_ADDR before believing anything else.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 4,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 1
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "up{job=\"vtop-engine\"}",
          "legendFormat": "up"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 1
              }
            ]
          },
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNonNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "area",
        "textMode": "value_and_name",
        "justifyMode": "center"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Verification failures (1h)",
      "description": "ANY non-zero value is an incident: an uploaded object did not match its manifest. The engine refuses to commit, so no data is lost - but the batch is stuck and needs a human.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 5,
        "x": 4,
        "y": 1
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(increase(vtop_verification_failures_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[1h])) or vector(0)",
          "legendFormat": "failures"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 1
              }
            ]
          },
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNonNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "area",
        "textMode": "value_and_name",
        "justifyMode": "center"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Batches failed (1h)",
      "description": "Batches that hit FAILED for any reason (compression, upload, verification). Source progress was never advanced, so they are replayable.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 5,
        "x": 9,
        "y": 1
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(increase(vtop_failed_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[1h])) or vector(0)",
          "legendFormat": "failed"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 1
              }
            ]
          },
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNonNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "area",
        "textMode": "value_and_name",
        "justifyMode": "center"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Replays required (1h)",
      "description": "Batches re-read from source after a failure. Safe by design, but a sustained rate means work is being repeated.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 5,
        "x": 14,
        "y": 1
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(increase(vtop_replay_required_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[1h])) or vector(0)",
          "legendFormat": "replays"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "orange",
                "value": 1
              }
            ]
          },
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNonNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "area",
        "textMode": "value_and_name",
        "justifyMode": "center"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "In-flight batches",
      "description": "Accumulated but not yet sealed. Climbing without bound means sealing has stalled; a steady sawtooth is just the max_batch_age timer doing its job.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 5,
        "x": 19,
        "y": 1
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "vtop_inflight_batches or vector(0)",
          "legendFormat": "in-flight"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNonNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "area",
        "textMode": "value_and_name",
        "justifyMode": "center"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "The core rule: SOURCE_COMMITTED is forbidden until VERIFIED",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 5
      },
      "collapsed": false,
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Verified vs committed (committed must never exceed verified)",
      "description": "The protocol's whole promise, made measurable. Commits happen only after verification, so the committed line must never rise above the verified line. If it does, the guarantee is broken - that is a P0, not a graph anomaly.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 6
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(rate(vtop_verified_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "verified/sec"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(rate(vtop_commits_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "committed/sec"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Invariant margin: verified - committed (must stay >= 0)",
      "description": "The same rule as a single number. >= 0 always. Small positive values are normal (a batch verified but not yet committed). A NEGATIVE value means a commit happened without a verification.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 6
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(vtop_verified_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}) - sum(vtop_commits_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"})",
          "legendFormat": "verified - committed"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Pipeline funnel",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 14
      },
      "collapsed": false,
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Batches entering each state (per sec)",
      "description": "Where batches stop. verified and source_committed should track each other; a gap that persists means batches are verifying but not committing.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 15
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (state) (rate(vtop_batches_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{state}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Verification strength",
      "description": "Backend-limited means verified by SIZE/EXISTENCE only, with no checksum - a weaker guarantee than the protocol intends. In production set upload.require_strong_verification: true so these are refused rather than committed.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 15
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(rate(vtop_verified_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "verified (total)"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(rate(vtop_verification_backend_limited_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "backend-limited (size only)"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Throughput",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 23
      },
      "collapsed": false,
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Records/sec",
      "description": "Derived from a counter with rate(), not exported as a gauge - a gauge of a rate lies between scrapes.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 24
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (format) (rate(vtop_records_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{format}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Bytes in vs out",
      "description": "The gap between the lines is what compression saves on the wire - and upload is the documented bottleneck, so this is the number that matters for throughput.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 8,
        "y": 24
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(rate(vtop_bytes_in_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "uncompressed in"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum(rate(vtop_bytes_out_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "compressed out (on the wire)"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          },
          "unit": "Bps"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Compression ratio (p50 / p95)",
      "description": "uncompressed/compressed; higher is better. A collapse toward 1.0 means the data shape changed or compression is effectively off.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 16,
        "y": 24
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.5, sum by (le) (rate(vtop_compression_ratio_bucket{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p50"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(vtop_compression_ratio_bucket{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Latency (histograms, so the tail is visible)",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 31
      },
      "collapsed": false,
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Per-stage p95",
      "description": "Which stage owns the time. object_upload usually dominates - the state store is NOT the bottleneck, which is why the HA plan puts effort into uploads rather than the database.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 32
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le, stage) (rate(vtop_stage_duration_seconds_bucket{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "{{stage}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          },
          "unit": "s"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "End-to-end batch latency (p50/p95/p99)",
      "description": "Batch start to source-committed. NOTE: batches seal on max_batch_age (60s by default), so on an idle lab this measures the timer, not slowness.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 32
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.5, sum by (le) (rate(vtop_batch_duration_seconds_bucket{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p50"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(vtop_batch_duration_seconds_bucket{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(vtop_batch_duration_seconds_bucket{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\", format=~\"$format\"}[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p99"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          },
          "unit": "s"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Sources",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 40
      },
      "collapsed": false,
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Source read errors/sec",
      "description": "A failed read is skipped and retried next cycle, so it is survivable - but a steady rate means a source is unhealthy and nobody would otherwise notice. Not labelled by source name: file/syslog names are full paths and a rotated file set would mint a series per file - the path is in the log panel beside this one. (No $format filter: a read fails before the format is known.)",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 41
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "mimir"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (source_type) (rate(vtop_source_read_errors_total{tenant=~\"$tenant\", source_type=~\"$source_type\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{source_type}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {}
    },
    {
      "type": "logs",
      "title": "Recent engine warnings and errors",
      "description": "Logs carry the high-cardinality detail (batch_id, object URI) that must never be a metric label. When a stat above goes red, the reason is here.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "loki"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 41
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "loki"
          },
          "expr": "{service=\"vtop-engine\"} | level=~\"WARN|ERROR\"",
          "queryType": "range"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "showTime": true,
        "wrapLogMessage": true,
        "sortOrder": "Descending"
      }
    }
  ]
}
